The paper discusses geometric data summarization, which is a topic that intersects with several subfields of computer science. The most relevant subfield is computational geometry (cs.CG), which deals with algorithms and data structures for geometric problems. The paper also discusses data structures and algorithms for handling large data sets (cs.DS), as well as techniques for clustering and density estimation (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions high-dimensional vectors and point sets, which are topics in machine learning and data mining (cs.SI, cs.LG).
